column1: Did the decision state the landlord was represented?
column2: Did the tenant propose a payment plan?
column3: If the tenant did propose a payment plan, did the member accept the proposed payment plan?
column4: Did the decision state the tenant was represented?
column5: If the tenant had a history of arrears, did the decision mention a history of the tenant making payments on those arrears (separate from any payments made in response to the present eviction notice/hearing)?
column6: Did the decision state that the tenant had children living with them?
column7: Was the tenant employed at the time of the hearing?
column8: If the tenant was not employed, did the decision state the tenant was receiving any form of government assistance (e.g. OW, childcare benefits, ODSP, OSAP)?
column9: If the tenant was employed, did the decision state any doubts about the stability of employment e.g. lack of guaranteed hours, contract work, etc.?
column10: Did the member find the tenant had sufficient income to pay rent?
